x
 2^{x+1} = 5^x 
 \begin{align*} 2^{x+1} &= 5^x\\ (x + 1)\ln 2 &= x \ln 5\\ x\ln 2 + \ln 2 &= x \ln 5\\ x \ln 2 - x \ln 5 &= -\ln 2\\ x(\ln 2 - \ln 5) & = -\ln 2\\ x &= \frac{\ln2}{\ln5 - \ln 2} \end{align*} 
2^{x+1} = 2^x \cdot 2^1
2 = 5^x / 2^x = (5/2)^x
a^{b+c}=a^b a^c
